<div class="jumbotron py-4 mb-3">
  <h1 class="display-4">Another Triple Triad Tracker</h1>
  <p class="lead">Another website for tracking your Final Fantasy XIV Triple Triad card collection.</p>
  <hr class="my-4">
  <h5>Why would you make another one of these?</h5>
  <p>
    I don't know, I just have a habit of
    <%= link_to 'remaking things that already exist', 'http://na.lodestone.raelys.com/', target: '_blank' %>.
  </p>
  <h5>What's so special about this one?</h5>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Easy setup:</b> Create and maintain your card collection by matching up the website with your in-game card list.</li>
      <li><b>Quick updates:</b> As much info as possible is pulled from the game data thanks to
        <%= link_to 'Saint Coinach', 'https://github.com/ufx/SaintCoinach', target: '_blank' %>.
      <li><b>Community:</b> If you have any feedback or feature requests, I want to hear them!</li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <div class="mt-4 text-center">
    <%= link_to 'Discuss on Discord', 'https://discord.gg/Bf62wNU', class: 'btn discord mt-2', target: '_blank' %>
    <%= link_to 'Support on Patreon', 'https://www.patreon.com/raelys', class: 'btn patreon mt-2', target: '_blank' %>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <h5>API</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p>
          All of the data used on this site is available for any savvy developers through a public RESTful JSON API.
          You can check out the full documentation
          <%= link_to 'here', 'https://github.com/mattantonelli/ffxiv-triple-triad/wiki', target: '_blank' %>.
        </p>
        <b>GET <%= link_to nil, api_card_url(240), class: 'unstyled' %></b>
        <%= render 'api_sample' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
